claim.claim-text:
26. The method of claim 22, wherein adjusting the width of the positive pulse of the square wave comprises: 
generating clock signals at a different rate depending on the predetermined pulse width; 
determining whether a lithography enable signal is input; 
if the lithography enable signal has been input, generating the square pulse while counting the number of clock signals until the result of the counting equals a predetermined number, such that the positive pulse is sustained during the predetermined pulse width.
